  "title": "Head of College Programmes [SL]",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Provide leadership and oversight for the daily operations and administrative functions of the college.</li>\n  <li>Supervise, mentor, and support faculty and staff to ensure effective performance.</li>\n  <li>Oversee the design, relevance, and continual evaluation of the curriculum and educational quality.</li>\n  <li>Ensure the recruitment and retention of highly qualified and dedicated teachers.</li>\n  <li>Plan and implement orientation and development programmes for new teachers and students.</li>\n  <li>Foster strong partnerships with parents, guardians, and the wider community.</li>\n  <li>Manage all aspects of student affairs, including strategic planning for recruitment, placement, scholarships, and the administration of student programmes.</li>\n  <li>Develop, monitor, and manage the college’s annual budget.</li>\n  <li>Promote efficient resource utilization and ensure the financial sustainability of the college.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Postgraduate degree in the relevant field.</li>\n  <li>NIE-trained and has held similar position in government secondary schools or colleges.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with ‘O’ and ‘A’ level programmes is a definite advantage.</li>\n  <li>Excellent people and leadership skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd | EA License No: 20C0270</p>\n<p>EA Personnel No: R22110981| EA Personnel Name: Law Mei Fong</p>",
